<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">MODFLOW Hydrogeologic Units Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">MODFLOW Hydrogeologic Units Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MODFLOW Hydrogeologic Units</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to define the hydrogeologic units in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="HUF2_Hydrogeologic_Unit_Flow" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Hydrogeologic Unit Flow (HUF2)</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package. </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MODFLOW Hydrogeologic Units</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is displayed by selecting </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Model|MODFLOW Hydrogeologic Units...</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">To define the hydrogeologic units of a MODFLOW model, the user adds or removes hydrogeologic units using the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Add hydrogeologic unit</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="AddLayer.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Add Layer Group button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Insert hydrogeologic unit</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="InsertLayer.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Insert Layer Group button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Delete </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">hydrogeologic unit</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text><image src="DeleteLayer.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Delete Layer Group button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> buttons on the left hand side of &#160;the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Hydrogeologic Units</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The main properties of each the hydrogeologic unit is specified by selecting the hydrogeologic unit in the list of hydrogeologic units on the left and entering appropriate values on the tabs to the right. The user can select multiple hydrogeologic units by holding down the Ctrl key when selecting hydrogeologic units.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MODFLOW Hydrogeologic Units</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box has three tabs: </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Properties_TabHUF" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Parameters_Tab" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Parameters</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Print_Tab" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Print</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
